Reasoning: The paper discusses message-passing algorithms for approximate inference in graphical models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents a unified view of convergent message-passing algorithms, which involves optimization and convergence analysis, making it relevant to computer science theory (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of these algorithms in control systems (cs.SY).
